docs.summary: Creates a query to retrieve a list of guests.
description: The `queryGuests()` function builds a query to retrieve a list of guests and returns a [GuestsQueryBuilder](https://www.wix.com/velo/reference/wix-events-v2/guests/guestsquerybuilder) object.
The returned object contains the query definition which is typically used to run the query using the `find()` function.

You can refine the query by chaining `GuestsQueryBuilder` functions onto the query. `GuestsQueryBuilder` functions enable you to sort, filter, and control the results that `queryGuests.find()` returns.
The query runs with the following `GuestsQueryBuilder` defaults that you can override:

The functions that are chained to `queryGuests()` are applied in the order they are called. For example, if you apply `ascending ('_createdDate')` and then `descending ('_updatedDate')`, the results are sorted first by the created date and then, if there are multiple results with the same date, the items are sorted by the updated date.

The table below shows which `GuestsQueryBuilder` functions are supported for `queryGuests()`. You can only use one filter function for each property. Only the first filter will work if a property is used in more than one filter.

members.name: cursor
members.doc:
Pointer to the next or previous page in the list of results.

You can get the relevant cursor token
from the `pagingMetadata` object in the previous call's response.
Not relevant for the first request.

members.name: limit
members.doc: Number of items to load per page.

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to previous page in the list of results.

members.name: _id
members.doc:
Unique event ID.
Allows clients to ignore duplicate webhooks.

members.name: entityEventSequence
members.doc:
A sequence number defining the order of updates to the underlying entity.
For example, given that some entity was updated at 16:00 and than again at 16:01,
it is guaranteed that the sequence number of the second update is strictly higher than the first.
As the consumer, you can use this value to ensure that you handle messages in the correct order.
To do so, you will need to persist this number on your end, and compare the sequence number from the
message against the one you have stored. Given that the stored number is higher, you should ignore the message.

members.name: entityFqdn
members.doc:
Assumes actions are also always typed to an entity_type
Example: wix.stores.catalog.product, wix.bookings.session, wix.payments.transaction

members.name: entityId
members.doc: ID of the entity associated with the event.

members.name: originatedFrom
members.doc: If present, indicates the action that triggered the event.

members.name: slug
members.doc:
This is top level to ease client code dispatching of messages (switch on entity_fqdn+slug)
This is although the created/updated/deleted notion is duplication of the oneof types
Example: created/updated/deleted/started/completed/email_opened

members.name: triggeredByAnonymizeRequest
members.doc:
Whether the event was triggered as a result of a privacy regulation application
(for example, GDPR).

members.name: currentEntityAsJson
members.doc:
Since platformized APIs only expose PATCH and not PUT we can't assume that the fields sent from the client are the actual diff.
This means that to generate a list of changed fields (as opposed to sent fields) one needs to traverse both objects.
We don't want to impose this on all developers and so we leave this traversal to the notification recipients which need it.

members.name: timestamp
members.doc: Event deleted timestamp in ISO UTC format.

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: Date and time the guest was created in `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sssZ` format.

members.name: _updatedDate
members.doc: Date and time the guest was updated in `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sssZ` format.

members.name: attendanceStatus
members.doc:
Attendance status.

**Note:** For `guestType` `BUYER` or `TICKET_HOLDER` the `IN_WAITLIST` value is not applicable.

members.name: attendanceStatusUpdatedDate
members.doc: Date and time of guest's latest attendance status update.

members.name: contactId
members.doc: Guest's contact ID. See [Contacts API](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/contacts-v4) for more details.

members.name: guestDetails
members.doc:
Guest details.

Returned only when the `guestDetails` fieldset is sent in the request.

members.name: guestType
members.doc:
Guest type:

`RSVP`: An invited guest, no ticket necessary.

`BUYER`: The guest who bought the tickets.

`TICKET_HOLDER`: The guest for whom the ticket was bought.

members.name: locale
members.doc: Locale in [IETF BCP 47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IETF_language_tag) format. Used when the event date and time on a ticket should be formatted into another locale.

members.name: orderNumber
members.doc:
Order number.

**Note:** Only applicable when `guestType` is `BUYER` or `TICKET_HOLDER`.

members.name: rsvpId
members.doc:
RSVP ID.

**Note:** Only applicable when `guestType` is `RSVP`.

members.name: secondaryLanguageCode
members.doc: Secondary language code in [ISO 639-1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) format. Used when the event ticket should be translated into another language.

members.name: ticketNumber
members.doc:
Ticket number.

**Note:** Only applicable when `guestType` is `TICKET_HOLDER`.

members.name: tickets
members.doc: List of names, numbers, and definition IDs for each ticket.

members.name: totalGuests
members.doc: Number of current guest plus additional guests

members.name: index
members.doc: Index in the RSVP guest list.

members.name: totalEventGuests
members.doc: Total guest count. For Rsvp Event every RSVP guest and additional guest count, for Ticketed Event count of TICKET_HOLDER

members.name: checkedIn
members.doc: Whether the guest has checked into the event.

members.name: onlineConferencingLogin
members.doc: The login details for the guest to access the online conference event.

members.name: grandTotal
members.doc:
Total amount of cart after discount, tax, and fees.
Grand total is calculated in the following order:
1. Total prices of all items in the cart are calculated.
2. Discount is subtracted from the cart (if applicable).
3. Tax is added (if applicable).
4. Wix service fee is added.

members.name: previewUrl
members.doc: URL to invoice preview. Returned only if order is paid.

members.name: revenue
members.doc: Total revenue, excluding fees. (Taxes and payment provider fees are not deducted).

members.name: subTotal
members.doc: Total cart amount before discount, tax, and fees.

members.name: discount
members.doc: Discount applied to the line item.

members.name: total
members.doc: Total price for line items. Always equal to price * quantity.

members.name: identity

members.name: currency
members.doc: ISO 4217 format of the currency i.e. `USD`.

members.name: value
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string with a period as a decimal separator (e.g., 3.99). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

members.name: query
members.doc: Query options. See [API Query Language](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/api-query-language) for more details.

members.name: cursorPaging
members.doc: Cursor token pointing to a page of results. Not used in the first request. Following requests use the cursor token and not `filter` or `sort`.

members.name: fieldsets
members.doc:
Currently the only supported fieldset is `guestDetails`. The `WIX_EVENTS.READ_GUESTS_DETAILS` permission is required to access the guest details.

See [field projection](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/field-projection) for more information.

members.name: filter
members.doc:
Filter object in the following format:
`"filter" : { "fieldName1": "value1", "fieldName2":{"$operator":"value2"} }`.

**Example:**
`"filter" : { "eventId": "sd3f-jhds-4fs77", "ticketNumber": {"$startsWith":"478"} }`

See [supported fields and operators](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/wix-events/wix-events/filter-and-sort) for more information.

members.name: paging
members.doc: Paging options to limit and skip the number of items.

members.name: sort
members.doc:
Sort object in the following format:
`[{"fieldName":"sortField1"},{"fieldName":"sortField2","direction":"DESC"}]`

**Example:**
`[{"fieldName":"createdDate","direction":"DESC"}]`

See [supported fields](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/wix-events/wix-events/filter-and-sort) for more information.
